Step 1: Update Your pom.xml
Add this INSIDE the <project> tag:

xml
<project>
    <!-- Your existing pom.xml above... -->

    <distributionManagement>
        <repository>
            <id>github</id>
            <name>GitHub Packages</name>
            <url>https://maven.pkg.github.com/Mohammed2023-224/SeleniumAutomation</url>
        </repository>
    </distributionManagement>

    <!-- Make sure you have these coordinates -->
    <groupId>com.yourcompany</groupId>  <!-- NOT io.github! -->
    <artifactId>selenium-framework</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0</version>

    <!-- Rest of your pom.xml... -->
</project>

Step 2: Get GitHub Token
Go to GitHub â†’ Settings â†’ Developer settings â†’ Personal access tokens â†’ Tokens (classic)

Click "Generate new token (classic)"

Name: "Maven Deployment"

Select scopes: âœ… repo âœ… write:packages âœ… read:packages

Generate token â†’ COPY IT! (you won't see it again)

Step 3: Set Token as Environment Variable
bash
# Mac/Linux
export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_copied_token_here

# Windows (Command Prompt)
set GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_copied_token_here

# Windows (PowerShell)
$env:GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_your_copied_token_here"

Step 4: Deploy Your Framework
bash
# Go to your framework project
cd /path/to/SeleniumAutomation

# Deploy to GitHub Packages
mvn clean deploy

Step 5: Verify Deployment
Go to: https://github.com/Mohammed2023-224/SeleniumAutomation/packages

You should see: selenium-framework 1.0.0

YOU'RE DONE! Now tell your team.

ðŸ“‹ PART 2: WHAT YOUR TEAM DOES (Framework Users)
Step 1: Team Updates Their pom.xml
Add this to THEIR project's pom.xml:

xml
<project>
    <!-- Inside the <project> tag, add: -->

    <!-- 1. Add GitHub repository -->
    <repositories>
        <repository>
            <id>github</id>
            <url>https://maven.pkg.github.com/Mohammed2023-224/SeleniumAutomation</url>
        </repository>
    </repositories>

    <!-- 2. Add your framework dependency -->
    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.yourcompany</groupId>
            <artifactId>selenium-framework</artifactId>
            <version>1.0.0</version>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <!-- Rest of their pom.xml... -->
</project>
Step 2: Team Gets GitHub Token
Each team member needs their OWN token:

Each person goes to their GitHub â†’ Settings â†’ Developer settings

Generate token with: âœ… read:packages

Save token

Step 3: Team Sets Up Authentication
Create ~/.m2/settings.xml (for each team member):

Mac/Linux: vim ~/.m2/settings.xml
Windows: C:\Users\Username\.m2\settings.xml

xml
<settings>
    <servers>
        <server>
            <id>github</id>
            <username>Mohammed2023-224</username>  <!-- YOUR username -->
            <password>ghp_their_personal_token_here</password>  <!-- THEIR token -->
        </server>
    </servers>
</settings>
OR Use Environment Variable (easier):

bash
# Team sets this once
export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_their_personal_token_here
Step 4: Team Uses Your Framework
bash
# Just normal Maven commands!
mvn clean compile    # Downloads your framework automatically